## Module Interfaces

All modules must implement `registry.Module`:

```go
type Module interface {
    Name() string
    Initialize(r *registry.Registry) error
    RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)
    RegisterGateway(ctx context.Context, mux *runtime.ServeMux, conn *grpc.ClientConn) error
}
```

### Optional Interfaces

#### ModuleMigrations

Implement to enable automatic migration discovery:

```go
func (m *Module) MigrationPath() string {
    return "modules/mymodule/resources/db/migration"
}
```

#### ModuleSeeder

Implement to enable automatic seed data discovery:

```go
func (m *Module) SeedPath() string {
    return "modules/mymodule/resources/db/seed"
}
```

#### ModuleAuth

Implement to declare public endpoints:

```go
func (m *Module) PublicEndpoints() []string {
    return []string{
        "/mymodule.v1.MyService/PublicMethod",
    }
}
```

#### ModuleLifecycle

Implement for startup/shutdown hooks:

```go
func (m *Module) OnStart(ctx context.Context) error {
    // Called after all modules initialized
    return nil
}

func (m *Module) OnStop(ctx context.Context) error {
    // Called during graceful shutdown
    return nil
}
```

#### ModuleHealth

Implement for custom health checks:

```go
func (m *Module) HealthCheck(ctx context.Context) error {
    // Return error if module is unhealthy
    return nil
}
```

### Module Registration

In `cmd/server/setup/registry.go`:

```go
// RegisterModules registers all modules with the registry.
func RegisterModules(reg *registry.Registry) {
    reg.Register(auth.NewModule())
    reg.Register(order.NewModule())
    reg.Register(payment.NewModule())
}
```

Migrations, seed data, and public endpoints are automatically discovered!
